@iftex
@unnumbered Preface

This manual documents the use and simple customisation of the af mail
reader and composer.  The reader is not expected to be a programmer;
simple customisations do not require programming skills.  If you are not
interested in customising then you can ignore the customisation hints.
This manual is primarily intended as a reference manual, but can also be
used as a primer.

To find the documentation on a particular command, look in the index.
Keys (character commands) and command names have separate indexes.
There is also a glossary, with a cross reference for each term.

This manual is available as a printed book and also as an Info file,
which can be browsed on-line using either GNU Emacs or the info program
from the GNU project.  The Info file and the printed book contain
substantially the same text and are generated from the same source
files, which are distributed along with af.
@end iftex

